Guard empty/nil event payloads in callEventCallback (nim-ffi 0.1.x).

`callEventCallback` passes `unsafeAddr event[0]` (and `unsafeAddr msg[0]` in the
except branch) to the C `FFICallBack`. For an empty Nim string the data pointer
is nil, so `event[0]` dereferences nil -> SIGSEGV on the first empty-payload
event (in practice: first peer connect, via the health monitor's
connection_status_change event).

Upstream issue: https://github.com/logos-messaging/nim-ffi/issues/139
Fixed on nim-ffi master (unreleased); every released tag (v0.1.3/4/5) is
affected, and logos-delivery pins v0.1.3.

Apply with -p1 inside the vendored nimble package directory
(nimbledeps/pkgs2/ffi-0.1.3-*/) AFTER `make build-deps` has populated it.

--- a/ffi/ffi_context.nim
+++ b/ffi/ffi_context.nim
@@ -36,14 +36,18 @@
     try:
       let event = body
       cast[FFICallBack](ctx[].eventCallback)(
-        RET_OK, unsafeAddr event[0], cast[csize_t](len(event)), ctx[].eventUserData
+        RET_OK,
+        (if len(event) > 0: unsafeAddr event[0] else: nil),
+        cast[csize_t](len(event)), ctx[].eventUserData
       )
     except Exception, CatchableError:
       let msg =
         "Exception " & eventName & " when calling 'eventCallBack': " &
         getCurrentExceptionMsg()
       cast[FFICallBack](ctx[].eventCallback)(
-        RET_ERR, unsafeAddr msg[0], cast[csize_t](len(msg)), ctx[].eventUserData
+        RET_ERR,
+        (if len(msg) > 0: unsafeAddr msg[0] else: nil),
+        cast[csize_t](len(msg)), ctx[].eventUserData
       )
 
 proc sendRequestToFFIThread*(
